# LWC Best Practices

Lightning Web Components should be designed for maintainability, performance, and scalability.

## 1. Keep Components Small and Reusable

Create focused components with a single responsibility.

### Example

```text id="g2pnv0"
AccountList Component
ContactList Component
Dashboard Component
```

---

## 2. Use @wire When Appropriate

Benefits:

* Automatic data refresh
* Improved performance

### Example

```javascript id="cn5t5x"
@wire(getAccounts)
accounts;
```

---

## 3. Handle Errors Properly

Example:

```javascript id="4k7j1w"
.catch(error => {
    console.error(error);
});
```

Benefits:

* Better user experience
* Easier troubleshooting

---

## 4. Avoid Unnecessary Re-renders

Update only required data.

Benefits:

* Faster UI performance
* Reduced browser load

---

## 5. Follow Naming Conventions

Example:

```text id="tjlwmj"
accountDashboard
contactManager
salesReport
```

Benefits:

* Better readability
* Easier maintenance

---

## 6. Separate Frontend and Backend Logic

### Frontend

* User interface
* User interactions

### Backend

* Business logic
* Database operations

Benefits:

* Cleaner architecture
* Better scalability

